rComments: His classes were so boring but he's a cool guy. You can't rely on only the slides or textbook, you have to go to class to do well on the midterms and final. I didn't even study for the final nor did I bother much with the cheat sheet either because I knew that the only way to get an A would have been to memorize the entire textbook.
He's a very cool lecturer and has a nice spirit. Plus, he allowed us to have cheat sheets which always came in clutch. Take his class, you won't regret it!

Very nice and caring man. Makes extremely boring content somewhat bearable. Sometimes hard to keep up during lectures. After both midterms and final I thought I did horribly but ended up with 'B's. Term paper is extremely opened to creativity and brings up your grade. Overall I was stressed but did fine. Recommend!

Professor Paré was my favourite professor this term. He is very clear on what he expects on assignments and is happy to help with student questions. His exams and assignments are fair. The class material can be a bit dull, but he manages to make the lectures interesting. I would definitely recommend taking his class!
Super fair prof. Content is boring, but the prof makes up for it.
Daniel Pare is by far the best proffesor! Would definitly recomend and definetly hope I have more classes with him in the future.
it's not an easy class but its fun.

Great prof! His lecturers are a ton of fun and make you want to go to class even if it's firs thing on a Monday morning. His test are fair in questions but he allows a cheat sheet. Easy A with a little bit of work.
He talks fast and sometimes mumbles but prepare for class and ask questions when needed - you should be fine.
well-prepared for lectures, happy to discuss papers cheat sheets allowed for exams
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']

rComments: Daniel Paré is an inspirational and engaging lecturer. Even though the content (especially the readings) could be really dry - he still emphasized the importance of knowing the facts and how they are relevant. His lectures were never disappointing. Exams are fair - just take good notes, ask questions and read the textbook! Lovely man, 10/10!

Prof. Pare is a good guy, but it was easy to get lost in his lectures because the content is so dry. Be prepared to actively take detailed notes throughout the whole lecture. Midterms and the exam are fair, but he asks about specific things that are mentioned in class so be sure to attend the lectures! Overall, I didn't enjoy the course.

Loved this guy! There is a lot to know in this class so you will be doing a lot of reading. All exams are multiple choice and he allows cheat sheets which are very helpful. His lectures are very interesting and he incorporates current life events to course content. Class was very well planned out and his expectations were very clear.
teacherRatingTags: ['Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read', 'Amazing lectures ']

rComments: EXTREMELY wonderful prof. Amazing lecture style, engages students to come to class. His expectations for you are clear, and he is fair. All examinations are multiple choice, and he lets you bring in a 'cheat sheet.' Very easy class such that you attend and do the readings. Engage with him, he's there for his students!

Pretty good teacher. Some classes can be pretty boring but that's just the material. You will probably hate him for the first week until you get use to this teaching style, must show up and take notes! The exams are extremely fair but a mix of things he only said in class and things in the textbook he doesn't mention at all. MUST READ EVERY PAGE

Daniel is a really good prof. He always states that his tests will be fair, and they have been so far. He is a really nice guy who likes to put daily events into his lectures. The only downsides are that there is a lot of reading and he does not have office hours. Tests are all multiple choice, but aren't super easy.

This professor is great and is very engaging. The lectures are fun but sometimes the material gets very theoretical so just pay attention in class and attend the lectures. He also cares about his students and is always available for help. Great class!

He is a good prof. His lectures are very heavy. Uses powerpoint slides. You have to attend the lectures. The textbook is used.  Allows you to use a cheat sheet on midterms. 2 midterms, 1 essay, and exam. It's not easy but you can do it!

Great class! Lots of reading, but mostly very interesting stuff. Great in-class discussions. Dan really knows his stuff (information communications technology, ICT), but doesn't dominate the conversation. Let's students have their say as well. Topics were very timely and interesting.

Good prof, relates things well to students, but be ready to apply yourself. You'll need to write a lot of notes in class, and the large textbook is not completly covered in lectures, but he will still ask, so be ready to read. But great class and prof, favorite in my first year, almost took a com. minor because of him. Also fair exams, just know it

Took Media Studies with him, our class had the use of cheat sheets, without them I doubt we would have managed. A LOT of content. DO attend class. He's so smart and I feel like he has a background in economics and it influences his lectures (which is a great thing). What else? He's very approachable, knowledgable, would definitely recommend!
All I have to say is if you attend the lectures, you'll do well! His exams focus a lot on what's said & viewed in class. He also makes the material interesting.

I thought the class would be difficult, but it was actually quite easy. Attend every class, take thorough notes & read the textbook and you should do well. Prof. Pare is awesome. He manages to make somewhat dry content interesting and he seems like he genuinely cares about his students' learning.

Great Proff! Clear and engaging lectures made time fly. Learned a lot. Read the text with your notes and the textbook beside you to have a better understanding when studying. You're allowed single side cheat sheet for both midterms and double for the final. :) Very helpful and passionate about his lectures. I would take other classes of his again.

Best advice I can give is attend lectures. He gives ample opportunities to do well in his class if you show up for lectures. If he plays a movie, don't leave because he will put questions on the mid term and exam based on the movie. Also I found him quite engaging. Exams had a lot of questions on royal commissions, so be aware of the differences
Although he may be a tough teacher he is extremely helpful and goes to great lengths to help you understand as long as you show interest!

this class was so horribly boring and confusing. his slideshows mainly consist of photos, thus there is very little on them and you must actively take note for 3 hours, the readings were long and equally as boring. exams are brutal.
Best advice with this prof is to read the assigned chapter before going to the lecture. Very dry material and lectures feel like they take forever. It was an 'okay' class.

Attend the lectures, as his exam has many questions about the class discussions. Participating with this class will drastically improve your understanding of the media, and Pare does the subject matter great justice. Skim the Chapters, do the online tests every week (20 minutes tops) and engage in the lectures, you'll get an A.

Not a good prof, or a good class. The class is entirely based on the textbook, so class attendance is pointless. All he did was drone on and on about communication policies which you have to memorize. The final was 180 multiple choice questions, which were all from the textbook, and the exact same questions as the previous 2 midterms. Avoid!

Extremely difficult class. If you break focus for even 3 seconds during his lecture, you will miss an important question on the packed exam filled with info you NEVER remember learning. Dreadful.. The exam was 28 pages long. Although I learned lots, and did relatively well (A-), it was probably one of the scariest classes of my life.

Don't take Media Studies with him for a 3 hour lecture. His lectures are rushed, there are only 3 exams (including the final), and there is way too much information to ever know. Doing well in this class is not easy.

Very good lecturer, he makes you interested in the topic even if the interest wasn't there to beging with. there is Alot of reading that will be overwelhming so start early if you can becasue they are all relevant. Overall I would take more classes with him.
Knows his stuff and very clear with his expectations. Interesting and kind. Moderate to hard marker. Great Prof.
He's a good lecturer, no complaints.
Really great professor! He obviously loves what he's teaching about and it makes the class that much better.

Pare's classes are always interesting. If you have not had Pare in the past you might be overwhelmed by course material at first, however, if you do the work you will get alot out of his classes. He is extremely knowledgeable and provides very useful feedback on assignments. Be prepared to do a substantial amount of reading and a 15 pg paper.

Awesome guy.... I usually sit at the back or in middle rows but i ended up sitting up front on the first row because the class was pack, and actually don't regret it! I was very much interested in what he was saying... DON'T EXPECT AN EASY GRADE THOUGH!

Great prof and a really nice guy. Extremely helpful and incites provocative discussion during seminars and lectures. Clearly an expert in his field -- the man can answer just about anything! I would suggest this prof to anyone but expect to work for your grade.

Pare is a fantastic prof. But he expects you to work for your A. Be aware that he has somekind of reading fetish, so you are expected to do at least 6 hours of reading a week to stay afloat during his lectures. One hint though, he rewards students for showing up to the final class......

Course was more interesting than I expected, all group presentations. Very fair marker and will go above and beyond to help you out and clarify expectations for assignments. Really cares about his students.  you don't really need to do the readings!
Pretty easy course, interesting prof, go to class, to the readings and the mid-term should be easy

Pare is ok in the non-boring department, I learned alot of interesting things in the class. The work load is ridiculous as far as reading goes. You have about 2 readings from 2 different books a week and they're about 15 pages long each. He also doesn't give you much guidance as far as the mid-term and final go. failed me by half a point on midterm
I LOVE HIM. best. prof. ever.

The Silver Fox is the best prof in CMN, hands down, and he isn't arrogant from the fact that all the CMN girls are in love with him. Do your readings and have an opinion on what's being discussed, and you cannot fail. Outside of class, he is *ridiculously* helpful. I hope I get him again and again and again!

Paré is my most favourite prof ever. Makes boring stuff interesting, willing to help out with any problems, fair marker, and an absolutely incredibly beautiful man. I could watch him pace back and forth across the room ALL DAY.
i miss his lectures
Good teacher (clear,presents solid material, nopersonal rants/bsing, just good, interesting stuff)A refreshingly serious,quality professor and anice guy

Nice professor, hard marker!!! I was not a fan of the "unannounced quiz"...more like the "unannounced exam"! It was not cool that he gave the class like 2 days notice to study for the midterms! p.s. we have other classes!!!
pare is an awesome prof. he is always available for one on one assistance. he makes his lectures interesting and informative. and he is gorgeous
Good guy teaching boring class. Policy Studies can put the more hardcome insomniac to sleep. Don't take the course unless you have to, but don't avoid other classes just because Pare is teaching it.

he's a great prof. his lectures are interesting (not straight out of the text, etc.-he really tries) and his exams and papers are fair. Overall, his classes are hard work, but you learn a lot and it's a good experience. Very nice and helpful.

Pare is a great lecturer! He makes a schedule and sticks to it. His tests and exams are very fair, and if you've gone to class and done your readings, there's nothing tricky about it. It also helps he's easy on the eyes. When you need help his office is open to students.
thought he was cute till he gave me a****ty mark...hard ass marker
Super nice, and hot too.  Very helpful.  Tries to make things clear, but usually teaches tough subjects.  Really good teacher though, makes boring class not so bad.

Prof Pare is awesome! He makes the oh-so-boring subject of Comm Policy and tries to make it fun - usually he succeeds.  He's funny and sweet, and very understanding of special situations.  And he's the hottest prof at OttawaU.

good prof. very thorough, very helpful. You'll learn a lot. Seems like he can jump quickly to the wrong conclusions though, often negative...watch out. Overall though, I recommend taking a course with him; it's enjoyable. Nice eyes...
He seemed to know what he was doing... and, of course, it helps when you can drool during the lectures... HOT!
Intelligent, approachable, and strives to be clear (versus purposely obscure!).  Endearing smile and premature grey combined with a real passion for his research and communication issues, he's a gem.
pretty good teacher, lots of material.  Has the hot older 'Richard Geere' kinda look with the earring.  Nice to look at and learn from.
Total babe-- love the earring. Britsh slang-very amusing! Kinda
Goes pretty fast, but the class is interesting.  He knows what he's doing.
Great prof! Makes the course really interesting.
No Comments
It was policy studies. He's extremely vague and disorganized. The entire course was basically nonsense. That might just be policy in general, but I'm not sure I can be that generous.
